## (4)(c) Convert dBm to Watts

> Assume that the 5G received power is $P_r$ = -72 dBm. What will be the receive power in Watts? *(5 marks)*

---

**Formula:**

$$P(\text{mW}) = 10^{\frac{P(\text{dBm})}{10}}$$

**Step 1: Calculate power in mW**

$$P = 10^{\frac{-72}{10}} = 10^{-7.2} = 6.31 \times 10^{-8} \text{ mW}$$

**Step 2: Convert mW to Watts**

$$P = 6.31 \times 10^{-8} \times 10^{-3} = 6.31 \times 10^{-11} \text{ W}$$

> **Answer: $P_r$ = 63.1 pW** (picowatts), or $6.31 \times 10^{-11}$ W

This is a very weak signal, but 5G receivers can work with signals as low as -100 dBm.
